## Coverage matrix (surface → authoritative doc)

Every surface the ADR touches must appear here.

| Surface | Authoritative doc | What must be explicitly defined |
| --- | --- | --- |
| CLI commands, flags, defaults | `<doc>` | names, defaults, precedence, exit-code implications |
| Config file paths, precedence, schema | `<doc>` | paths, precedence, schema constraints |
| Exit code meanings | `<doc>` | mapping to taxonomy, overrides if any |
| Environment variables | `<doc>` | name, type, allowed values, default, precedence |
| Protocol surface | `<doc>` | message shapes, errors, timeouts, ordering |
| Data schema or file format | `<doc>` | schema, constraints, canonicalization |
| Telemetry or log fields | `<doc>` | field names, types, redaction rules |
| Filesystem semantics | `<doc>` | invariants, path rules, failure modes |
| Platform parity or divergence | `<doc>` | guarantees, divergences, validation evidence |

## Determinism checklist

For every selected document, confirm it explicitly defines:
- inputs and precedence order when multiple inputs exist
- defaults and absence semantics
- data model and constraints for every serialized boundary
- error model and failure posture
- ordering, atomicity, or concurrency rules if any
- security and redaction invariants if any
- platform guarantees if any

